These are the times, my friends. And these are the days. Where the world becomes malleable, palpable. When novelty and genius are within our reach. We are cautioned against being passionate about these things by tales of progress turned to greed and of technology turning on us. And yet, the golden light is just right, the clocks are synchronizing, the stars are in alignment. This is what we celebrate tonight. We celebrate these transient times, with these transient artists. - c. lantz WAYFARERS OF THE GYPSY MANSION - a musical bazaar of sorts with HUMANWINE, BLACKBIRD ORCHESTRA, NATHANIEL JOHNSTONE, TOY BOX TRIO, MEISCE, FINN VON CLARET, and DJ Q. Sunday, May 10, 2009 3 pm to 10 pm The Little Red Studio 750 Harrison Street, Seattle, WA ALL-AGES, $15 donation Wearables, craftables, and edibles provided by a plethora of local and regional artisans. We will take a dinner break (with DJ) at 6:30 pm - please bring your own sack meal, a picnic to share, or food can be acquired from two of our vendors. Vegan options available. Adult beverages can be purchased by 21+ individuals.

HOLY SHIT!!! The Red King will be playing Seattle May 1st for free. The Show takes place in Anderson Park, Capitol Hill (1635 11TH AVENUE), SEATTLE. FRIDAY, MAY 1st : 7PM sharp. Very excited about this!

If you have ever wondered what the Carnival in Venice is like, here is your opportunity. There will be Music, Costumes and Coffee provided by Tully's. For one evening only, we will bring a little of the Carnival to Seattle! I will be showing new photos from my many trips to the Carnival in Venice Italy.. There will be music, coffee, amazing costumes and kick ass photos!

I had the opportunity to shoot another really cool show this last Sunday… The Ghosts Project, Jill Tracy, Nathaniel Johnstone, Magpie Killjoy, Schrödinger's Cat. I can’t really adequately describe this show; there was something different about it. So I guess I really will not try. I will say however that this was one of the best shows I have ever attended. I cannot explain why, it just was. My hope is that I captured even a little bit of that vibe..
